# Apple dunkelgrün

When the user says **„apple dunkelgrün“**, they mean the background gradient from Apple’s **Active Noise Cancellation gallery** on [airpods-pro](https://www.apple.com/airpods-pro/) — class `.section-variant` in `overview.built.css`.

Reference only — do not apply unless the user explicitly asks to use it in UI.

## Gradient

```css
background: linear-gradient(rgb(22, 23, 19), rgb(59, 59, 49));
/* equivalent */
background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #161713, #3b3b31);
```

| Stop | RGB | Hex |
|------|-----|-----|
| Top | `rgb(22, 23, 19)` | `#161713` |
| Bottom | `rgb(59, 59, 49)` | `#3b3b31` |

- **Type**: simple 2-stop linear gradient, default direction top → bottom
- **Character**: warm dark olive / near-black, not pure gray or pure green
- **Typical pairing**: white or `rgba(255,255,255,.8)` body copy on top

## Related Apple tokens on same section

- Near-black text on light overlays: `#1d1d1f`

## Do not confuse with

- **Apple gray surfaces** (`#f5f5f7`) — see `festag-apple-gray-surfaces.mdc`
- Mesh / radial marketing gradients on other Apple product pages
